  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/16307</id>
    <published>2012-09-20T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-09-20T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/number-of-newly-registered-ultra-low-emissions-vehicles"/>
    <title>Number of newly registered ultra low emissions vehicles</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;h2 id="dft-business-plan"&gt;DfT Business plan&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id="geographical-coverage-united-kingdom"&gt;Geographical coverage: United Kingdom&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3 id="information-broken-down-by-data-available-by-la-on-request-published-quarterly"&gt;Information broken down by: Data available by LA on request, published quarterly.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h2 id="latest-data"&gt;Latest data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the second quarter of 2012 (April-June), 961 new ultra-low emission vehicles were registered for the first time in the UK. 
Most recent data:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://charts.dft.gov.uk/dft-business-plan/indicators/#06"&gt;Click here to view this data in an interactive chart&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Quarter&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;New UK registrations of ultra-low emission vehicles&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;2011  Apr-Jun&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;628&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;2012  Apr-Jun&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;628&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Percentage change&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;+53%&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/veh01-vehicles-registered-for-the-first-time"&gt;The complete data table is available here:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 961 ultra-low emission vehicles registered for the first time in quarter 2 2012 represents an increase of 53 per cent from the figure of 628 in the same quarter of the previous year. Most of these vehicles use electric engines, so the Plug-In Car Grant introduced by DfT in January 2011, and an increase in the supply of electric cars to the UK market will have contributed to this increase. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="https://assets.digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/10538/veh0170.xls"&gt;VEH0170&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="background-information"&gt;Background information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Department for Transport uses the term ‘ultra-low emission vehicles’ to refer to vehicles with significantly lower levels of tailpipe emissions than conventional vehicles. In practice, the term currently refers to electric, plug-in hybrid and hydrogen fuel-cell vehicles.  Vehicles that use non-fossil fuel propulsion have zero tailpipe emissions. For other propulsion types, only vehicles with tailpipe emissions below 75 grams per kilometre are included. The figures are produced from DVLA’s and DVA’s new registration system and only vehicles being registered in Great Britain or Northern Ireland for the first time are included. 
There is a high level of seasonal variation in new vehicle registrations (for example higher sales when registration plates change in September and April), therefore it is misleading to compare data for consecutive quarters. Comparisons should be made with the same quarter of previous years.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;publishing schedule: Quarterly&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;last updated: 13 September 2012&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;next update: December 2012&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel="external" href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20111005174110/http:/assets.dft.gov.uk/publications/adobepdf-about-717940-717943/input-01.pdf"&gt;Measurement template&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="other-related-data-and-information"&gt;Other related data and information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport/series/vehicle-licensing-statistics"&gt;Vehicle Licensing Statistics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

