&lt;h3 id="geographical-coverage-dft-franchised-train-operators-great-britain"&gt;Geographical coverage: DfT franchised train operators (Great Britain)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3 id="information-broken-down-by-train-operator"&gt;Information broken down by: Train operator&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h2 id="latest-data"&gt;Latest data&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;92.3% of trains arrived on time between 16 September 2012 and 13 October 2012 in Great Britain, an increase from 91.5% for the same period last year (GB total). The GB average headline figure incorporates Public Performance Measure (&lt;abbr title="Public Performance Measure"&gt;PPM&lt;/abbr&gt;) averages for operators franchised by devolved administrations (Arriva Trains Wales, First Scotrail, London Overground and Merseyrail), and non-franchised operators (Grand Central, Heathrow Express and Hull Trains), however, the following table covers only DfT franchised operators.&lt;/p&gt;

